# OPS/_llm/100 — the doc's success criterion: log + change the model.
#
# `.request` is the client's Anthropic Messages JSON; whatever this
# stack leaves there is what the upstream receives, byte for byte. Here
# we pin every request to a cheaper model and tag the upstream call
# with a header so the rewrite is visible on the wire. The trace
# (`txco trace`) is the request log — every gateway request shows up as
# an ordinary traced pipeline run.
#
# Gate on the phase: without it, request-shaping rules would re-run on
# the fire-and-forget completion envelope (phase "completed") that
# arrives after the stream ends.
# NOTE: pin a model id that EXISTS upstream — a stale id here makes
# Anthropic 404 every request, and the client (correctly) sees that 404
# verbatim but misattributes it to ITS selected model, which reads as
# "the gateway is broken".
WHEN @src == "llm" && @llm.phase == "request"
  EMIT .request.model = "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
       @llm.headers.x-txco-llm-policy = "model-pinned"
